byline.contributor: Arielle Dollinger reported from Setauket, and William Neuman from New York. Noah Remnick contributed reporting from New York.
byline.original: By ARIELLE DOLLINGER and WILLIAM NEUMAN

abstract: Suffolk County, LI, police continue to search for 23-year-old City College student Gerson Salmon-Negron, who was on board single-engine plane that was forced to land in water of Setauket Harbor off North Shore of Long Island; other three men on plane were rescued.

headline.print_headline: College Student Missing After Plane Lands in Harbor Off Long Island
headline.main: College Student Missing After Plane Lands in a Long Island Harbor

snippet: After a single-engine plane made a forced landing in Setauket Harbor, the police searched for a 23-year-old City College student. The three other passengers were rescued.
lead_paragraph: After a single-engine plane made a forced landing in Setauket Harbor, the police searched for a 23-year-old City College student. The three other passengers were rescued.
